      "abstract": "A systematic and rapid steepest-ascent numerical procedure is described for determining optimum programs for nonlinear systems with terminal constraints. The procedure uses the concept of local linearization around a nominal (nonoptimum) path. The effect on the terminal conditions of a small change in the control variable program is determined by numerical integration of the adjoint differential equations for small perturbations about the nominal path.",
      "summary": "One of the foundational papers on gradient-based trajectory optimization, introducing the use of adjoint-equation integration to compute the steepest-ascent direction for optimal control problems with terminal constraints. The adjoint (co-state) approach is the direct predecessor of modern shooting methods and continuous-time policy gradient algorithms.",
