      "abstract": "This paper investigates solutions Xhat of the algebraic Riccati equation F'X + XF - XGG'X + Q = 0 with the property Re lambda(F - GG'Xhat) <= 0. The uniqueness and existence of such a solution is completely characterized. In addition, the conditions are strengthened to characterize the important stabilizing solution (Re lambda(F - GG'Xhat) < 0). All standard existence results are recovered as special cases.",
      "summary": "Characterizes the stabilizing solution of the algebraic Riccati equation arising in LQR design, establishing necessary and sufficient conditions for its existence and uniqueness. A key reference for the theoretical foundations of Riccati-based optimal control synthesis.",
